news.title: Top auditors stop offering non-audit work
news.para: Top audit firms in India, including KPMG affiliate BSR & Affiliates and BDO affiliate MSKA & Associates, have stopped offering non-audit services to audit clients.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates Haryana stretch of Dwarka Expressway
news.para: On March 9, 2019 the then Union ministers, Sushma Swaraj, Arun Jaitley and Nitin Gadkari had laid the foundation stone for Dwarka Expressway.

news.title: Kerala: Seven sand mining sites identified in Periyar and Muvattupuzha
news.para: A total of 82,190 cubic metres of sand is available at the seven sites in the two major rivers, out of which 25,500 cubic metres can be extracted for mining purpose, the report said.

news.title: JM Financial Home Loans aims to grow AUM to Rs 5,000 crore by FY26
news.para: The company has a capital base of Rs. 450 crore and a leverage of three times. It is also looking to further increase its presence in Maharashtra, Gujarat, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka and Tamil Nadu.

news.title: Telangana CM to launch Indiramma housing scheme
news.para: He will leave for Yadagirigutta from Begumpet airport in a chopper and offer prayers along with a couple of ministers. Later, he will heli-hop to Bhadrachalam and offer prayers at Seetha Ramachandra Swamy temple.

news.title: Over 1,000 families receive homes under PMAY-Urban in Azamgarh
news.para: These houses, constructed using a cutting-edge PVC stay-in-place formwork technology, boast disaster-resistant and eco-friendly features, setting a new standard for affordable housing projects in India.

news.title: RHB issues 37 leases to house owners in Jaipur's Pratap Nagar
news.para: The public hearing program was organized on Sunday at Circle Office Pratap Nagar for hearing and quick disposal of the complaints and problems of the common people in a transparent and sensitive environment.

news.title: Surat-based builder cheated of Rs 4 crore by three partners, cops begin probe
news.para: The victim was Magan Desai and the accused were Mehul Lakhani, Virendra Lakhani and their father Labhu Lakhani. They forged documents and sold land belonging to their partnership firm.

news.title: MahaRERA cancels registration of 13,785 real estate agents
news.para: The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) has cancelled the registration of 13,785 real estate agents who failed to renew their licenses.

news.title: Jaipur development body’s panel to approve building plans
news.para: Now, zonal offices of the JDA won’t be able to give permissions for construction of buildings. A building plan should get approved only at the building map committee level.

news.title: Asset reconstruction companies vie for ACCIL Corp's Jaipur hotel debt
news.para: Last month, Omkara ARC beat competitor Asset Reconstruction Company of India (Arcil) with a ₹38 crore cash offer to Chennai-based Indian Bank in a Swiss challenge.

news.title: NARCL offers Rs 10,000 crore for Jaiprakash Associates' loans
news.para: In the case of JAL, State Bank of India has the largest debt hold at 26%, followed by ICICI Bank at 19% and IDBI Bank at 11%. The company has total principal outstanding debt of ₹17,700 crore as of March 2023.

news.title: Mumbai airport rehabilitation flats 'sold' right after possession
news.para: Last Friday, a function was held at a private banquet hall in Andheri where the local MLA handed over keys of 53 PAP flats. Saki Naka police said some of the recipients illegally sold their flats after receiving the keys outside the banquet hall.

news.title: Villas in Manikonda face bulldozer action for encroaching on Neknampur lake
news.para: Over a dozen multi-crore villas in Manikonda near Neknampur Lake are being demolished due to being constructed illegally in the buffer zone.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body to unveil housing project with 700 units
news.para: The housing project is being developed at Subuddhipur on the city outskirts, which will have over 700 dwelling units, the highest ever in any BDA project while the urban forest just adjacent to it, is being developed over a whopping area of 90 acres.

news.title: Stuck RG Luxury Homes project in Greater Noida West now offers possession
news.para: The 18-acre project, RG Luxury Homes, in Greater Noida West was launched in 2010 with an initial deadline of 2014. Facing delays, the construction work was stalled in 2016 due to a fund crisis.

news.title: PM virtually inaugurates light house project in Ranchi
news.para: At a programme in Ranchi, 10 beneficiaries were handed over keys of houses as token distribution, director of Directorate of Municipal Administration Aditya Kumar Anand said.

news.title: Rajasthan government invites bids for 14 sand mining blocks in two districts
news.para: Previously, the department had proposed auctions for 22 blocks in Tonk, Sawai Madhopur, Nagaur, and other districts, but these were recently stayed by the Rajasthan High Court.
